The paper discusses the conflicts between traditional Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC) models and blockchain enabled smart contract based applications, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. It also addresses the immutability of blocks and contracts, which relates to the security and cryptography (cs.CR) category. The use of blockchain technology also involves distributed computing (cs.DC) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the need for new standard models to address the arising issues suggests a focus on systems and information theory (cs.SI).
